o to its ___.","wiki"),("libel","5","Defamation  is the oral or written communication of a false statement about another that unjustly harms their reputation and usually constitutes a tort or crime. communicating a true statement can also be considered defamation.","wiki"),("ranks","5","The Table of ___  was a formal list of positions and ___ in the military, government, and court of Imperial Russia. Peter the Great introduced the system in 1722 while engaged in a struggle with the existing hereditary nobility, or boyars. The Table of ___ was formally abolished on 11 November 1917 by the newly established Bolshevik government.","wiki"),("bhima","5","After 18 days of war, Duryodhana went and hid under a lake. After given option to choose opponent & kind of duel, Duryodhana chose ___ as his opponent & mace fight as duel. ___ clashed with Duryodhana in a mace fight. Though ___ had superior strength, Duryodhana started dominating. Lord Krishna knew that it is not possible to kill Duryodhana because Duryodhana's body turned as tough as a diamond with power in Gandhari's eyes. Krishna instrucuted ___ to hit Duryodhana's thighs through gestures. ___ did as Krishna directed & successfully broke thighs of Duryodhana. Enraged at this sight, Balarama grabbing his plough paced to attack ___, but was stopped by Krishna. Krishna convinced his brother by narrating the injustice death of A___nyu and evils committed by Duryodhana.","wiki"),("ankam","5","___ is a Malayalam word meaning combat or battle. It may refer either to a duel or a larger scale war. In medieval Kerala, ___ served as a way to settle disputes between districts and nobles. The duellists, called Chekavar or Ankachekavar, were trained in the kalari to fight as militiamen in service of a lord.","wiki"),("badik","5","The ___ or badek is a knife or dagger developed by the Bugis and Makassar people of southern Sulawesi, Indonesia.","wiki"),("truel","5","A ___ is a neologism for a duel among three opponents, in which players can fire at one another in an attempt to eliminate them while surviving themselves.","wiki"),("bando","5","As with most Asian martial arts, ___ schools start off by teaching the basic stances and footwork. This preliminary stage of training traditionally lasts for several months, although many instructors today avoid doing so. In the second stage of training, a series of blocking and parrying techniques is taught. ___ prioritises defense over offense so that the student will be able to protect themselves should the need arise. The defensive approach is also meant to discourage aggression and teach students to apply their skills with care. Offensive moves are taught in the third stage.","wiki"),("arnis","5","There have been campaigns for ___ to be nominated in the UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage Lists, along with other Philippine martial arts. As of 2018, UNESCO has inscribed 9 martial-arts–related intangible heritage.","wiki"),("wuxia","5","___ , which literally means 'martial heroes', is a genre of Chinese fiction concerning the adventures of martial artists in ancient China. Although ___ is traditionally a form of fantasy literature, its popularity has caused it to spread to diverse art forms such as Chinese opera, mànhuà, films, television series and video games. It forms part of popular culture in many Chinese-speaking communities around the world.","wiki"),("plate","5","___ armour is a historical type of personal body armour made from bronze, iron or steel ___s, culminating in the iconic suit of armour entirely encasing the wearer. While there are early predecessors such as the Roman-era lorica segmentata, full ___ armour developed in Europe during the Late Middle Ages, especially in the context of the Hundred Years' War, from the coat of ___s worn over mail suits during the 14th century.","wiki"),("scale","5","___ armour  of various shapes attached to each other and to a backing of cloth or leather in overlapping rows. ___ armour was worn by warriors 